issue.title: [CF 929] Stun DR not tracking correctly
issue.body:
What steps will reproduce the problem?
1. Enable tracking of DR-ControlledStun on Target
2. Stun enemy target in pvp scenario
3. Observe the tracking functionality

What do you expect to happen? What happens instead?
Typically, it would show an icon of the last stun used on the target with a percentage of the DR for the stun on that target.  Instead TellMeWhen refuses to track Stun DRs of any kind.  Am not aware if this is the same for other types of DR.

What version of TellMeWhen are you using? ("The latest" is not a version)
6.2.6.  The most recent.

Do you have an error log of what happened?
I do not.

Please provide any additional information below (including any export strings if applicable; see above.)
I believe it stopped working correctly in the patch.


> Posted by CurseForge user backseatbunny | Imported from CurseForge issue #929 | Raw

comments.body:
Unable to reproduce. Stun DR tracking is working beautifully for me. Try upgrading to the latest alpha version (http://wow.curseforge.com/addons/tellmewhen/files/) and see if this fixes the problem.


> Posted by CurseForge user Cybeloras
